            <div class="media">
             <div class="pull-left">
              <img alt="[title_1]" src="https://globalstudies.uncc.edu/sites/globalstudies.uncc.edu/files/styles/news_image/public/fields/news/field_news_landscape_image/9781138931657%20%282%29.jpg?itok=mfns_Iqu"/>
             </div>
             <div class="media-body">
              <h3>
               Interview with UNCC prof. Emek Ergun and her co-editor on major new book
              </h3>
              <i aria-hidden="true" class="fa fa-calendar">
              </i>
              <span class="date-display-single">
               December 16, 2018
              </span>
              <br/>
              <p>
               <em>
                Feminist Transation Studies: Local and Transnational Perspectives
               </em>
               (Routledge, 2017) explores feminist approaches to translation across diverse geographical and historical locations as resistant transnational practices that challenge multiple forms of domination. In the piece, they introduce feminist translation studies, discuss the role that translation plays in the transnational and...
              </p>
              <p>
               <a alt=" Interview with UNCC prof. Emek Ergun and her co-editor on major new book" class="button button-green" href="/interview-uncc-prof-emek-ergun-and-her-co-editor-major-new-book" title=" Interview with UNCC prof. Emek Ergun and her co-editor on major new book">
                Read More
               </a>
              </p>
             </div>
            </div>
            <div class="clear_float">
            </div>
